PN,41601
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,FA farmer from Sussex has warned that
OL,8,Fthis unseasonably dry spring could
OL,9,Fhave major impacts for British
OL,10,Fconsumers later this year.
OL,12,FFrank Langrish says his farm near Rye,
OL,13,Fhas received only one millimetre of
OL,14,Frain since the start of March.
OL,16,FHe believes the situation will become
OL,17,F''very serious'' without a change in
OL,18,Fweather.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,FIf that doesn't happen, he fears it
OL,8,Fcould lead to higher prices on
OL,9,Fsupermarket shelves.
OL,11,FSpeaking to ITV Meridian, he said:
OL,12,F"There's been a strange set of
OL,13,Fcircumstances where grain prices have
OL,14,Fbeen particularly low, so it hasn't
OL,15,Fbeen particularly profitable to grow
OL,16,Fgrain.
OL,18,F"So farmers have cut back on the
OL,19,Famount they're producing.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,F"Any drop in production is going to
OL,8,Fhave an impact on prices."
OL,10,FFarmer James Cossins farms around 2000
OL,11,Facres at his property in Dorset, and
OL,12,Fshares the same concern.
OL,14,FHe's worried that his crop yields
OL,15,Fcould be down if the plants don't get
OL,16,Fthe water they need in the next few
OL,17,Fmonths.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,F"We haven't really had any appreciable
OL,8,Frain since the middle of March and our
OL,9,Fcrops - the spring sown crops are
OL,10,Fcertainly beginning to suffer," he
OL,11,Fsaid.
OL,13,F"We're about to plant some maize or we
OL,14,Fhave sown some maize already, but
OL,15,Fagain that needs moisture to get it
OL,16,Fgoing.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,F"Spring barley desperately needs
OL,8,Fmoisture and all the crops, grass,
OL,9,Fwinter crops desperately need moisture
OL,10,Fand looks like we could be going in
OL,11,Ffor another drought year like last
OL,12,Fyear."
OL,14,FJames said the winter crops seem to be
OL,15,Fable to come through but they are
OL,16,Fconcerns for the spring crops.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,F"With a lot of livestock to feed, you
OL,8,Fknow we rely heavily on grass, so
OL,9,Fwe're cutting the grass now to feed
OL,10,Fnext winter and we need good yields to
OL,11,Fmake sure that we can see see through
OL,12,Fthe winter.
OL,14,F"We've seen it before but it just
OL,15,Fseems virtually every year now we have
OL,16,Fan extreme - either too wet, too dry.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,F"We say we're getting used to it but
OL,8,Fthere's only so much we can take and
OL,9,Fwith other things going on on the
OL,10,Ffarm, and due to world issues, yeah
OL,11,Fit's all challenging."
OL,13,FBut for the regions vineyards', the
OL,14,Fdry spell could mean a bumper year for
OL,15,FBritish wine.
OL,17,FAt Exton Park Vineyard in Hampshire,
OL,18,Funlike other crops on the south coast,
OL,19,Fthe grapes here benefit from warm and
OL,20,Fdry weather.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,FVineyard director Fred Langdale said
OL,8,Fthey've had a decent temperature.
OL,10,F"That's made the vines get out of
OL,11,Fdormancy early in the April, which has
OL,12,Fbeen fantastic," he said.
OL,14,F"The only worry now, of course, is
OL,15,Fwe're more open to frost risks with
OL,16,Fthis early growth, but I think we're
OL,17,Fcoming to the end of April and we
OL,18,Fshould be all right by the middle of
OL,19,FMay.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1777449958
OL,3,CFarmers fear harvests will suffer if
OL,4,Cthe prolonged dry spell lasts much
OL,5,Clonger
OL,7,F"At this time of year, the vines are
OL,8,Fshowing about two bunches of
OL,9,Finflorescence of flowers, and if they
OL,10,Fget frosted off now, it would delay
OL,11,Four harvest until the end of October.
OL,13,F"But it really depletes the energy
OL,14,Fthat's in the vines."
